situation: Cal is watching his friend play basketball and sees his friend miss a shot.

situation: Malcolm is at home and his mother told him to do some chores for her before going out.
intention: Malcolm wants to get out of the house.

situation: James is demonstrating his passionate opposition to abortion by protesting outside a women's health clinic.

situation: Amber has a dog named Twinkie who loves to beg for scraps.

situation: Bane got new anti-lock brakes put into his car, and he liked them.

situation: Sue has two kids Mike and Bob which she is taking care of.
intention: Sue wants to raise her kids so that they turn out well.

situation: John's friend tells John not to eat the french fries, as they are fattening.

situation: Taylor is going to a potluck work Christmas party and needs to bring a dish to pass.

action_pairs: "Taylor makes pot brownies and takes them to the party with a sign reading, ""Double Chocolate Brownies""."
